   Architecture August 28, 2017
   Comments (1) Apartment

São Paulo Apartment Annex

   Architects from São Paulo based studio Vaga came up with the clever way
   to add space to a small home. They have built an annex that
   incorporates two bedrooms, a bathroom, and a rooftop deck. The sliding
   door allows switching between privacy and open use of the spaces. The
   rooftop deck is used for a herb garden and as an extra hang-out space.
   Cool modern idea. See more photos after the break.

   Via

